Hello Arun,

#2 is sort of outside the bounds of heritrix, but a couple of things come to mind. You can use the wayback (http://archive-access.sourceforge.net/projects/wayback/) to play back web pages stored in arcs or warcs. If you want to simply grab one record out of a warc (not arc) from the command line, the hanzo warc tools might be easiest (http://code.google.com/p/warc-tools/), specifically warcdump and wrecordbody.

Not sure about the threads. Perhaps take a look at the thread report and frontier report and see if anything looks fishy, copy&paste to this list if you&#39;re still puzzled.

Noah

